  "author": "SiteFlow Operations Team",
  "publishDate": "2026-06-26",
  "body": "\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-ddaadaf48381ce5bf6bd435dfa79c41f wp-block-paragraph\">An overview of the Reports section in SiteFlow — what reports are available, how to open and filter them, how to download them, and which article covers each category in detail.</p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-52978\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"448\" src=\"/images/recon/Add-a-heading-24-1024x448.webp\" width=\"1024\"/></figure>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Prerequisites</h2>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-b65bf4bc4b31a2c01b84a224a6419932\">\n<li>You need at minimum a role with Report access enabled. Admins and Senior Managers can see all reports by default.</li>\n<li>Some reports (Salary, Payroll) require Payroll data to be set up first. Others (Materials, PO) require data to be recorded in the respective modules.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to Open Reports</h2>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-3fce035c349e710cf4039fa237a8a1fe wp-block-paragraph\">Click <strong>Reports</strong> in the left sidebar.</p>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-d2ae59a5ef6a2ac0a6e6333ec4749e9f wp-block-paragraph\">The Reports page shows all 16 categories at a glance. Each category displays its individual report names.</p>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to Open and Filter a Report</h2>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-842232770262b7a36cce0adb633c85da wp-block-paragraph\">Each report has two icons:</p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Icon</th><th>What It Does</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Settings (gear) icon</strong></td><td>Opens the report in full view with all filters available. Use this when you want to apply date ranges, project filters, or party filters before downloading.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Download icon</strong></td><td>Downloads the report immediately with default filters, without opening the full view. Use this for quick exports when no custom filtering is needed.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-7a2d72812d314c938f3e421850540cd1 wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Common filters available inside most reports:</strong></p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Filter</th><th>What It Does</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Date Range</strong></td><td>Limit the report to a specific period</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Project</strong></td><td>Show data from one project or all projects</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Party</strong></td><td>Filter by a specific vendor, client, or subcontractor</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Status</strong></td><td>Filter by Paid, Unpaid, or Partially Paid where applicable</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-0b47370738ededd492392c814f9cd4bd wp-block-paragraph\">After applying filters, click <strong>Download PDF</strong> or <strong>Download Excel</strong> inside the report view.</p>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">All Report Categories</h2>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Sales</h3>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Report</th><th>What It Shows</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Company Sales Report</td><td>All sales invoices across all projects</td></tr><tr><td>Item Wise Sales Report</td><td>Sales broken down by line item</td></tr><tr><td>Deduction and Retention</td><td>Deductions and retention amounts across all invoices</td></tr><tr><td>CRM Lead Detail Report</td><td>Detailed CRM lead data</td></tr><tr><td>Lead Status Report</td><td>Status-wise summary of CRM leads</td></tr><tr><td>Project Wise Sales Summary</td><td>Sales totals per project</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-bc00e55f2a64e18a0a019b030f2107cd wp-block-paragraph\">For detailed guidance see: Guide to Using Sales Reports in SiteFlow.</p>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Payments</h3>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Report</th><th>What It Shows</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Company Payments</td><td>All payment transactions across the company</td></tr><tr><td>Bank Statement</td><td>Bank-wise transaction log</td></tr><tr><td>Project Wise Payment Summary</td><td>Payment totals per project</td></tr><tr><td>Project Payment Report</td><td>Detailed payment entries per project</td></tr><tr><td>Payment Request Report</td><td>Status of all payment requests across projects</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-40a16ce09aece1b41df2bcf5a78ddcbb wp-block-paragraph\">For detailed guidance see: Guide to Using Payment Reports in SiteFlow.</p>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Progress and Task</h3>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Report</th><th>What It Shows</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Daily Progress Report (DPR)</td><td>Work summary, labour, materials, equipment, and site photos for a date range</td></tr><tr><td>Task Report</td><td>Task-wise progress summary across projects</td></tr><tr><td>Task Measurement Book</td><td>Measurement entries recorded against tasks</td></tr><tr><td>Task Material Report</td><td>Materials allocated and used against tasks</td></tr><tr><td>To Do Report</td><td>To Do items and their status across projects</td></tr><tr><td>Task Resource Budget vs Actual</td><td>Planned vs actual resource usage per task</td></tr><tr><td>Site Inspection Report</td><td>Inspection findings across projects</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-a02c182d24c1d13511d473bf265889a2 wp-block-paragraph\">For detailed guidance see: Guide to Using Progress and Task Reports in SiteFlow and Daily Progress Report (DPR) in SiteFlow.</p>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Purchase and Expense</h3>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Report</th><th>What It Shows</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Company Expense Report</td><td>All expenses across the company</td></tr><tr><td>Cost Code Wise Expense Analysis</td><td>Expenses broken down by cost code category</td></tr><tr><td>Project Wise Expense Summary</td><td>Expense totals per project</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-b58e36ab7affeb22c76bcb2757b2dbd4 wp-block-paragraph\">For detailed guidance see: Guide to Using Purchase and Expense Reports in SiteFlow.</p>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Party Balances</h3>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Report</th><th>What It Shows</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Party Ledger</td><td>Full transaction history for a single party</td></tr><tr><td>All Party Balances</td><td>Outstanding balances across all parties</td></tr><tr><td>Project Level Party Balance Report</td><td>Party balances per project</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-1291e82cbc989c857e966004970a8f7d wp-block-paragraph\">For detailed guidance see: Guide to Using Party Balance Reports in SiteFlow.</p>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Materials and Inventory</h3>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Report</th><th>What It Shows</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Material Request Item Report</td><td>All material requests by item across projects</td></tr><tr><td>Material Received and Used Report</td><td>GRN vs consumption summary</td></tr><tr><td>Material Stock Report</td><td>Current stock levels across projects</td></tr><tr><td>Unbilled Item Report</td><td>Materials received but not yet invoiced</td></tr><tr><td>PO Summary Report</td><td>Purchase order summary</td></tr><tr><td>Material Received without PO</td><td>GRNs raised without a linked PO</td></tr><tr><td>Purchase Order Item Report</td><td>Item-wise PO details</td></tr><tr><td>Production Material Report</td><td>Materials used in production</td></tr><tr><td>Material Purchase Item Report</td><td>Purchase details by material item</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-afd2cf9ae67ce5edbb421566ec97d3e4 wp-block-paragraph\">For detailed guidance see: Guide to Using Materials and Inventory Reports in SiteFlow.</p>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Attendance and Salary</h3>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Report</th><th>What It Shows</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Attendance and Salary Report</td><td>Combined attendance and salary data</td></tr><tr><td>OT and Shift Report</td><td>Overtime and shift details</td></tr><tr><td>Company Attendance</td><td>Company-wide attendance summary</td></tr><tr><td>Staff Monthly Salary Slip</td><td>Salary slips for individual staff members</td></tr><tr><td>Staff Salary Report</td><td>Salary details per staff member</td></tr><tr><td>Staff Punch Report</td><td>Punch-in and punch-out log</td></tr><tr><td>Staff Muster Roll</td><td>Muster roll across projects</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-230d461df3ab4d34e6fa1de99eb40b7b wp-block-paragraph\">For detailed guidance see: Guide to Using Attendance and Salary Reports in SiteFlow.</p>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Equipment</h3>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Report</th><th>What It Shows</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Equipment Usage Detail Report</td><td>Detailed equipment usage log</td></tr><tr><td>Fuel Efficiency Report</td><td>Fuel consumption per equipment item</td></tr><tr><td>Daily Based Equipment Used Report</td><td>Day-wise equipment usage</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-76d8d1d05229e17f25dcb54228d97ebe wp-block-paragraph\">For detailed guidance see: Equipment Expense Summary Report.</p>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Asset</h3>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Report</th><th>What It Shows</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Asset Allocation Report</td><td>Which assets are assigned where across the company</td></tr><tr><td>Asset Status Report</td><td>Current status of all assets</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Tax</h3>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Report</th><th>What It Shows</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Sales — GSTR-1</td><td>GST output tax report for all sales invoices</td></tr><tr><td>Purchase — GSTR-2</td><td>GST input tax report for all purchase invoices</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Warehouse</h3>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Report</th><th>What It Shows</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Warehouse Stock Report</td><td>Current stock in each warehouse</td></tr><tr><td>Warehouse Transaction Report</td><td>All transactions in and out of warehouses</td></tr><tr><td>Warehouse Current Stock</td><td>Real-time stock snapshot across all warehouses</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Subcontractor</h3>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Report</th><th>What It Shows</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Subcon Workorder Summary Report</td><td>Summary of all subcontractor work orders</td></tr><tr><td>Subcon Measurement Book</td><td>Measurement book for subcontractor work</td></tr><tr><td>Deduction and Retention for Subcon</td><td>Deductions and retention held against subcontractors</td></tr><tr><td>Subcon Material Issue Summary</td><td>Materials issued to subcontractors</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Miscellaneous</h3>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Report</th><th>What It Shows</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Project Financial Summary</td><td>Overall financial summary per project (revenue, expense, margin)</td></tr><tr><td>Project Operational Summary</td><td>Operational metrics per project</td></tr><tr><td>Company Transactions Report</td><td>All financial transactions company-wide</td></tr><tr><td>PnL Report</td><td>Profit and Loss summary across the company</td></tr><tr><td>Project Activity Leaderboard</td><td>Activity ranking across projects</td></tr><tr><td>Company User Activity Leaderboard</td><td>User activity ranking across the team</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Library</h3>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-06516caa02d796d2fe810b636c3ccbb6 wp-block-paragraph\">Downloadable exports of all library data: Party Library, Cost Code Library, Material Library, Asset Library, Rate Card Library, Payroll Library, and Equipment Library.</p>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">BOQ</h3>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Report</th><th>What It Shows</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>BOQ</td><td>Full BOQ document for a project</td></tr><tr><td>BOQ Item Report</td><td>Item-wise BOQ data across projects</td></tr><tr><td>Quotation Report</td><td>All CRM quotations</td></tr><tr><td>Quotation Item Report</td><td>Item-wise quotation breakdown</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Budget</h3>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Report</th><th>What It Shows</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Bill of Material (BOM)</td><td>Material list with quantities from the project BOQ</td></tr><tr><td>Budget vs Actual — Material Cost</td><td>Planned material cost vs actual recorded cost</td></tr><tr><td>Budget vs Actual — Material Qty</td><td>Planned material quantities vs actual quantities used</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Tips</h2>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-560a0c7e5ed642c17c6da6f2cb5f4651\">\n<li>Use the <strong>Settings icon</strong> when you need to filter by date, project, or party before downloading. Use the <strong>Download icon</strong> when you want the full report quickly with default filters.</li>\n<li>Most reports default to the last 30 days. Always check the date range filter when the report opens to ensure it covers the period you need.</li>\n<li>The <strong>Party Ledger</strong> report is the fastest way to get a full transaction history for any vendor or client. Filter by party name and set the date range to cover the full project duration.</li>\n<li>The <strong>PnL Report</strong> and <strong>Project Financial Summary</strong> are the best starting points for a management review meeting. Both give a quick revenue vs expense overview across all projects.</li>\n<li>The <strong>Unbilled Item Report</strong> in Materials and Inventory identifies GRNs with no matching purchase invoice. Run this weekly to keep accounts payable accurate.</li>\n<li>The <strong>Cost Code Wise Expense Analysis</strong> is the most useful report for overhead tracking when expenses are recorded with consistent cost codes.</li>\n<li>Library reports (Material Library, Party Library, etc.) are useful for auditing master data — checking for duplicates or inconsistencies before a bulk upload.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">If Something Goes Wrong</h2>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Problem</th><th>Likely Cause</th><th>What to Do</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Cannot see the Reports section</td><td>Role does not have Report access</td><td>Ask Admin to check your role permissions and enable Download Reports</td></tr><tr><td>Report shows no data</td><td>Date range filter set incorrectly, or no data recorded for the selected period</td><td>Open the report via the Settings icon and adjust the date range</td></tr><tr><td>Report shows data from all projects but only one is needed</td><td>Project filter not applied</td><td>Open via the Settings icon, apply the Project filter, then download</td></tr><tr><td>Cannot download as Excel for a specific report</td><td>That report only supports PDF format</td><td>Check the download options inside the report. Not all reports support both formats.</td></tr><tr><td>Salary or attendance data missing from reports</td><td>Payroll not set up or attendance not recorded</td><td>Set up Payroll first and ensure attendance is being marked consistently</td></tr><tr><td>GSTR-1 report showing incorrect GST totals</td><td>Invoices created without correct GST percentage</td><td>Review invoices for the period and correct GST rates where needed</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n"
}